Lower meeting mode VAD threshold for hardware with quiet cpal capture.

On some hardware (e.g. Framework 16 with PDM mic via PipeWire ALSA
emulation), cpal captures at 44100Hz/2ch and the resulting 16kHz mono
audio has RMS well below the default 0.01 threshold, causing all
chunks to be rejected as silence despite the user speaking.

Lower the threshold to 0.0001 so only truly silent chunks are filtered.
The whisper transcriber already handles noisy/quiet audio well.

--- a/src/meeting/chunk.rs
+++ b/src/meeting/chunk.rs
@@ -26,7 +26,7 @@ impl Default for ChunkConfig {
     fn default() -> Self {
         Self {
             chunk_duration_secs: 30,
-            vad_threshold: 0.01,
+            vad_threshold: 0.0001,
             sample_rate: 16000,
             min_chunk_duration_secs: 0.5,
         }
